<article>
    <h1>Pay&#xAD;ment ser&#xAD;vice op&#xAD;tions for busi&#xAD;nesses IN&#xAD;STANT BANK TRANS&#xAD;FERS BY PAYNOW COR&#xAD;PO&#xAD;RATE</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201014/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-10-14"><time>2020-10-14</time></a>
        - <span>TOP OF THE NEWS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Wire­card, which sup­ports close to 1,900 credit card ac­cep­tance mer­chants here, has been or­dered to halt its pay­ment ser­vices.</p>
    <p>The Mon­e­tary Author­ity of Sin­ga­pore (MAS) is­sued the direc­tive on Sept 30 af­ter Wire­card said it was un­able to con­tinue pro­vid­ing pay­ment pro­cess­ing ser­vices to a sig­nif­i­cant num­ber of mer­chants here.</p>
    <p>Here are some al­ter­na­tives.</p>
    <p>PayNow Cor­po­rate is a quick and con­ve­nient way for busi­nesses to pay and re­ceive Sin­ga­pore dol­lar funds im­me­di­ately by link­ing their unique en­tity num­ber to a Sin­ga­pore bank ac­count.</p>
    <p>Busi­nesses can usu­ally sign up for PayNow Cor­po­rate quickly.</p>
    <p>They can then ac­cept e-pay­ment via a PayNow QR code. Cus­tomers who want to pay the busi­ness can do so with­out need­ing to know its bank and ac­count num­ber. For more in­for­ma­tion, go to the As­so­ci­a­tion of Banks in Sin­ga­pore web­site at www.abs.org.sg/mer­chan­tac­qui­si­tion</p>
    <p>SIN­GLE QR CODE PAY­MENTS BY SGQR</p>
    <p>SGQR com­bines mul­ti­ple pay­ment QR codes into a sin­gle SGQR la­bel that helps busi­nesses ac­cept pay­ments from a wide range of ser­vice providers, in­clud­ing banks and e-wal­let providers.</p>
    <p>It also means less clut­ter on the store front and quicker pay­ment pro­cess­ing. Read more de­tails at www.mas.gov.sg/devel­op­ment/ e-pay­ments/sgqr</p>
    <p>WIDE VA­RI­ETY OF PAY­MENT SER­VICES VIA E-WAL­LETS AND CARDS</p>
    <p>Busi­nesses can ac­cept pay­ments via e-wal­lets or cards by ap­proach­ing banks and non-bank fi­nan­cial in­sti­tu­tions, in­clud­ing Nets, that of­fer mer­chant ac­qui­si­tion ser­vices. More de­tails can be found on ABS and MAS web­sites.</p>


</article>

